@startuml Signup Flows - User Journey
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam activity {
    BackgroundColor #E8F4F8
    BorderColor #2C5F7C
    FontColor #1A3A4A
}
skinparam note {
    BackgroundColor #FFF9E6
    BorderColor #D4A574
}

title TWS ERP - Self-Serve Signup Flows (User Perspective)

|#LightBlue|**Common Entry Point**|
start
:User clicks "Start Free Trial" 
on landing page;
:System detects industry from URL;
note right
  URL patterns:
  - /healthcare → healthcare
  - /education → education
  - /software-house → software_house
  - /warehouse → warehouse
  - default → business
end note

|#LightGreen|**Step 1: Account Creation**|
:User fills registration form;
note right
  **Education Flow:**
  - First Name
  - Last Name
  - Email
  - Password (12+ chars)
  - Confirm Password
  
  **All Other Flows:**
  - Full Name
  - Email
  - Password (12+ chars)
  - Confirm Password
end note

:Client validates form;
:Client validates email format;
:Client checks email via API;
note right
  API: GET /api/email/validate?email=...
  Checks:
  - Format validation
  - Disposable email detection
  - MX record validation
end note

if (Email valid?) then (yes)
  :User submits form;
  :API: POST /api/signup/register;
  note right
    Backend:
    - Validates email
    - Checks if email exists
    - Hashes password
    - Creates user account
    - Generates OTP
    - Sends verification email
    Returns: userId, verificationId
  end note
else (no)
  :Show error message;
  :User corrects email;
  stop
endif

|#LightYellow|**Step 2: Email Verification**|
:User receives 6-digit OTP 
via email;
:User enters OTP code;
:User submits OTP;
:API: POST /api/signup/verify-email;
note right
  Backend:
  - Validates OTP
  - Checks expiry
  - Marks email as verified
  - Returns userId
end note

if (OTP valid?) then (yes)
  :Email verified successfully;
else (no)
  :Show error message;
  :User can resend OTP;
  :API: POST /api/signup/resend-otp;
  :Return to OTP entry;
  stop
endif

|#LightCoral|**Step 3: Industry-Specific Information**|

partition "Education Flow (5 steps)" {
  :User enters school information;
  note right
    Fields:
    - School Name
    - School Type (K-12/College/University)
    - School Email (optional)
    - School Phone (optional)
  end note
  
  :User enters tenant subdomain;
  :API: GET /api/signup/check-slug-availability?slug=...;
  note right
    Real-time validation:
    - Checks if slug is available
    - Validates format (3-50 chars, lowercase, numbers, hyphens)
    - Shows availability status
  end note
  
  if (Slug available?) then (yes)
    :Proceed to Step 4;
  else (no)
    :Show error;
    :User enters different slug;
    stop
  endif
  
  :User submits tenant details;
}

partition "Healthcare Flow (4 steps)" {
  :User enters facility information;
  note right
    Fields:
    - Hospital/Clinic Name
    - Facility Type (Hospital/Clinic/Medical Center/Pharmacy)
    - License Number (optional)
    - Contact Phone (optional)
    - Tenant Subdomain
  end note
  
  :API: GET /api/signup/check-slug-availability?slug=...;
  
  if (Slug available?) then (yes)
    :Proceed to Step 4;
  else (no)
    :Show error;
    :User enters different slug;
    stop
  endif
  
  :User submits tenant details;
}


partition "Software House Flow (4 steps)" {
  :User enters company information;
  note right
    Fields:
    - Company Name
    - Team Size (1-5/6-15/16-50/50+)
    - Primary Tech Stack (JS/Python/Java/.NET/etc.)
    - Development Methodology (Agile/Scrum/Kanban/etc.)
    - Tenant Subdomain
  end note
  
  :API: GET /api/signup/check-slug-availability?slug=...;
  
  if (Slug available?) then (yes)
    :Proceed to Step 4;
  else (no)
    :Show error;
    :User enters different slug;
    stop
  endif
  
  :User submits tenant details;
}

partition "Warehouse Flow (4 steps)" {
  :User enters warehouse information;
  note right
    Fields:
    - Warehouse/Company Name
    - Warehouse Type (Distribution/Fulfillment/Cold Storage/etc.)
    - Square Footage (optional)
    - Tenant Subdomain
  end note
  
  :API: GET /api/signup/check-slug-availability?slug=...;
  
  if (Slug available?) then (yes)
    :Proceed to Step 4;
  else (no)
    :Show error;
    :User enters different slug;
    stop
  endif
  
  :User submits tenant details;
}

partition "Business Flow (3 steps - minimal)" {
  :User enters organization information;
  note right
    Fields:
    - Organization Name
    - Tenant Subdomain
  end note
  
  :API: GET /api/signup/check-slug-availability?slug=...;
  
  if (Slug available?) then (yes)
    :Proceed to confirmation;
  else (no)
    :Show error;
    :User enters different slug;
    stop
  endif
  
  :User submits tenant details;
}

|#LightPink|**Step 4: Tenant Creation**|
:API: POST /api/signup/create-tenant;
note right
  Backend Process:
  1. Creates tenant record
  2. Assigns user as tenant admin
  3. Applies industry-specific template
  4. Creates onboarding checklist
  5. Triggers async provisioning:
     - Database setup
     - Default configurations
     - Welcome email
  6. Returns tenant details
end note

if (Tenant created?) then (yes)
  :Show success confirmation;
  note right
    Confirmation Screen:
    - "Your [Industry] ERP is being set up"
    - Progress indicator
    - Estimated setup time
  end note
else (no)
  :Show error message;
  :User can retry or contact support;
  stop
endif

|#LightGreen|**Step 5: Completion & Redirect**|
:Wait 3 seconds;
:Redirect to tenant subdomain;
note right
  Redirect URL:
  https://[slug].tws.example.com/onboarding
  
  User lands on:
  - Tenant-specific onboarding dashboard
  - Role-based checklist
  - Welcome message
end note

:User completes onboarding;
:User starts using ERP;
stop

@enduml
